157 VOID
158 MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool (
159  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
160  IN ULONG SizeInPages
161  )
162 
163 /*++
164 
165 Routine Description:
166 
167  This function protects freed nonpaged pool.
168 
169 Arguments:
170 
171  VirtualAddress - Supplies the freed pool address to protect.
172 
173  SizeInPages - Supplies the size of the request in pages.
174 
175 Return Value:
176 
177  None.
178 
179 Environment:
180 
181  Kernel mode.
182 
183 --*/
184 
185 {
186  ULONG i;
187  MMPTE PteContents;
188  PMMPTE PointerPte;
189  PMMPTE LastPte;
190  PVOID FlushVa[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
191 
192  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress)) {
193  return;
194  }
195 
196  //
197  // Prevent anyone from touching the free non paged pool.
198  //
199 
200  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
201  LastPte = PointerPte + SizeInPages;
202 
203  do {
204 
205  PteContents = *PointerPte;
206 
207  PteContents.u.Hard.Valid = 0;
208  PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype = 1;
209 
210  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, PteContents);
211 
212  PointerPte += 1;
213 
214  } while (PointerPte < LastPte);
215 
216  if (SizeInPages == 1) {
217  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VirtualAddress, TRUE);
218  }
219  else if (SizeInPages < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
220 
221  for (i = 0; i < SizeInPages; i += 1) {
222  FlushVa[i] = VirtualAddress;
223  VirtualAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)VirtualAddress + PAGE_SIZE);
224  }
225 
226  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (SizeInPages, &FlushVa[0], TRUE);
227  }
228  else {
229  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0xB);
230  }
231 
232  return;
233 }

236 LOGICAL
237 MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool (
238  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
239  IN ULONG SizeInPages
240  )
241 
242 /*++
243 
244 Routine Description:
245 
246  This function unprotects freed nonpaged pool.
247 
248 Arguments:
249 
250  VirtualAddress - Supplies the freed pool address to unprotect.
251 
252  SizeInPages - Supplies the size of the request in pages - zero indicates
253  to keep going until there are no more protected PTEs (ie: the
254  caller doesn't know how many protected PTEs there are).
255 
256 Return Value:
257 
258  TRUE if pages were unprotected, FALSE if not.
259 
260 Environment:
261 
262  Kernel mode.
263 
264 --*/
265 
266 {
267  PMMPTE PointerPte;
268  MMPTE PteContents;
269  ULONG PagesDone;
270 
271  PagesDone = 0;
272 
273  //
274  // Unprotect the previously freed pool so it can be manipulated
275  //
276 
277  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(VirtualAddress) == 0) {
278 
279  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress((PVOID)VirtualAddress);
280 
281  PteContents = *PointerPte;
282 
283  while (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0 && PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype == 1) {
284 
285  PteContents.u.Hard.Valid = 1;
286  PteContents.u.Soft.Prototype = 0;
287 
288  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, PteContents);
289 
290  PagesDone += 1;
291 
292  if (PagesDone == SizeInPages) {
293  break;
294  }
295 
296  PointerPte += 1;
297  PteContents = *PointerPte;
298  }
299  }
300 
301  if (PagesDone == 0) {
302  return FALSE;
303  }
304 
305  return TRUE;
306 }

309 VOID
310 MiProtectedPoolInsertList (
311  IN PLIST_ENTRY ListHead,
312  IN PLIST_ENTRY Entry,
313  IN LOGICAL InsertHead
314  )
315 
316 /*++
317 
318 Routine Description:
319 
320  This function inserts the entry into the protected list.
321 
322 Arguments:
323 
324  ListHead - Supplies the list head to add onto.
325 
326  Entry - Supplies the list entry to insert.
327 
328  InsertHead - If TRUE, insert at the head otherwise at the tail.
329 
330 Return Value:
331 
332  None.
333 
334 Environment:
335 
336  Kernel mode.
337 
338 --*/
339 {
340  PVOID FreeFlink;
341  PVOID FreeBlink;
342  PVOID VirtualAddress;
343 
344  //
345  // Either the flink or the blink may be pointing
346  // at protected nonpaged pool. Unprotect now.
347  //
348 
349  FreeFlink = (PVOID)0;
350  FreeBlink = (PVOID)0;
351 
352  if (IsListEmpty(ListHead) == 0) {
353 
354  VirtualAddress = (PVOID)ListHead->Flink;
355  if (MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool (VirtualAddress, 1) == TRUE) {
356  FreeFlink = VirtualAddress;
357  }
358  }
359 
360  if (((PVOID)Entry == ListHead->Blink) == 0) {
361  VirtualAddress = (PVOID)ListHead->Blink;
362  if (MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool (VirtualAddress, 1) == TRUE) {
363  FreeBlink = VirtualAddress;
364  }
365  }
366 
367  if (InsertHead == TRUE) {
368  InsertHeadList (ListHead, Entry);
369  }
370  else {
371  InsertTailList (ListHead, Entry);
372  }
373 
374  if (FreeFlink) {
375  //
376  // Reprotect the flink.
377  //
378 
379  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool (FreeFlink, 1);
380  }
381 
382  if (FreeBlink) {
383  //
384  // Reprotect the blink.
385  //
386 
387  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool (FreeBlink, 1);
388  }
389 }

464 VOID
465 MiTrimSegmentCache (
466  VOID
467  )
468 
469 /*++
470 
471 Routine Description:
472 
473  This function initiates trimming of the segment cache.
474 
475 Arguments:
476 
477  None.
478 
479 Return Value:
480 
481  None.
482 
483 Environment:
484 
485  Kernel Mode Only.
486 
487 --*/
488 
489 {
490  KIRQL OldIrql;
491  LOGICAL SignalDereferenceThread;
492  LOGICAL SignalSystemCache;
493 
494  SignalDereferenceThread = FALSE;
495  SignalSystemCache = FALSE;
496 
497  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
498 
499  if (MmUnusedSegmentForceFree == 0) {
500 
501  if (!IsListEmpty(&MmUnusedSegmentList)) {
502 
503  SignalDereferenceThread = TRUE;
504  MmUnusedSegmentForceFree = MmUnusedSegmentForceFreeDefault;
505  }
506  else {
507  if (!IsListEmpty(&MmUnusedSubsectionList)) {
508  SignalDereferenceThread = TRUE;
509  MmUnusedSegmentForceFree = MmUnusedSegmentForceFreeDefault;
510  }
511 
512  if (MiUnusedSubsectionPagedPool < 4 * PAGE_SIZE) {
513 
514  //
515  // No unused segments and tossable subsection usage is low as
516  // well. Start unmapping system cache views in an attempt
517  // to get back the paged pool containing its prototype PTEs.
518  //
519 
520  SignalSystemCache = TRUE;
521  }
522  }
523  }
524 
525  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
526 
527  if (SignalSystemCache == TRUE) {
528  if (CcHasInactiveViews() == TRUE) {
529  if (SignalDereferenceThread == FALSE) {
530  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
531  if (MmUnusedSegmentForceFree == 0) {
532  SignalDereferenceThread = TRUE;
533  MmUnusedSegmentForceFree = MmUnusedSegmentForceFreeDefault;
534  }
535  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
536  }
537  }
538  }
539 
540  if (SignalDereferenceThread == TRUE) {
541  KeSetEvent (&MmUnusedSegmentCleanup, 0, FALSE);
542  }
543 }

615 SIZE_T
616 MmAvailablePoolInPages (
617  IN POOL_TYPE PoolType
618  )
619 
620 /*++
621 
622 Routine Description:
623 
624  This function returns the number of pages available for the given pool.
625  Note that it does not account for any executive pool fragmentation.
626 
627 Arguments:
628 
629  PoolType - Supplies the type of pool to retrieve information about.
630 
631 Return Value:
632 
633  The number of full pool pages remaining.
634 
635 Environment:
636 
637  PASSIVE_LEVEL, no mutexes or locks held.
638 
639 --*/
640 
641 {
642  SIZE_T FreePoolInPages;
643  SIZE_T FreeCommitInPages;
644 
645 #if !DBG
646  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (PoolType);
647 #endif
648 
649  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() == PASSIVE_LEVEL);
650 
651  ASSERT (PoolType == PagedPool);
652 
653  FreePoolInPages = MmSizeOfPagedPoolInPages - MmPagedPoolInfo.AllocatedPagedPool;
654 
655  FreeCommitInPages = MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum - MmTotalCommittedPages;
656 
657  if (FreePoolInPages > FreeCommitInPages) {
658  FreePoolInPages = FreeCommitInPages;
659  }
660 
661  return FreePoolInPages;
662 }

665 LOGICAL
666 MmResourcesAvailable (
667  IN POOL_TYPE PoolType,
668  IN SIZE_T NumberOfBytes,
669  IN EX_POOL_PRIORITY Priority
670  )
671 
672 /*++
673 
674 Routine Description:
675 
676  This function examines various resources to determine if this
677  pool allocation should be allowed to proceed.
678 
679 Arguments:
680 
681  PoolType - Supplies the type of pool to retrieve information about.
682 
683  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes to allocate.
684 
685  Priority - Supplies an indication as to how important it is that this
686  request succeed under low available resource conditions.
687 Return Value:
688 
689  TRUE if the pool allocation should be allowed to proceed, FALSE if not.
690 
691 --*/
692 
693 {
694  KIRQL OldIrql;
695  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
696  SIZE_T FreePoolInBytes;
697  LOGICAL Status;
698  MM_POOL_PRIORITIES Index;
699 
700  ASSERT (Priority != HighPoolPriority);
701  ASSERT ((PoolType & MUST_SUCCEED_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == 0);
702 
703  NumberOfPages = BYTES_TO_PAGES (NumberOfBytes);
704 
705  if ((PoolType & BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == NonPagedPool) {
706  FreePoolInBytes = ((MmMaximumNonPagedPoolInPages - MmAllocatedNonPagedPool) << PAGE_SHIFT);
707  }
708  else if (PoolType & SESSION_POOL_MASK) {
709  FreePoolInBytes = MmSessionPoolSize - (MmSessionSpace->PagedPoolInfo.AllocatedPagedPool << PAGE_SHIFT);
710  }
711  else {
712  FreePoolInBytes = ((MmSizeOfPagedPoolInPages - MmPagedPoolInfo.AllocatedPagedPool) << PAGE_SHIFT);
713  }
714 
715  Status = FALSE;
716 
717  //
718  // Check available VA space.
719  //
720 
721  if (Priority == NormalPoolPriority) {
722  if ((SIZE_T)NumberOfBytes + 512*1024 > FreePoolInBytes) {
723  if ((PsGetCurrentThread()->MemoryMaker == 0) || (KeIsExecutingDpc ())) {
724  goto nopool;
725  }
726  }
727  }
728  else {
729  if ((SIZE_T)NumberOfBytes + 2*1024*1024 > FreePoolInBytes) {
730  if ((PsGetCurrentThread()->MemoryMaker == 0) || (KeIsExecutingDpc ())) {
731  goto nopool;
732  }
733  }
734  }
735 
736  //
737  // Paged allocations (session and normal) can also fail for lack of commit.
738  //
739 
740  if ((PoolType & BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == PagedPool) {
741  if (MmTotalCommittedPages + NumberOfPages > MmTotalCommitLimitMaximum) {
742  if (PsGetCurrentThread()->MemoryMaker == 0) {
743  MiIssuePageExtendRequestNoWait (NumberOfPages);
744  goto nopool;
745  }
746  }
747  }
748 
749  //
750  // If a substantial amount of free pool is still available, return TRUE now.
751  //
752 
753  if (((SIZE_T)NumberOfBytes + 10*1024*1024 < FreePoolInBytes) ||
754  (MmNumberOfPhysicalPages < 256 * 1024)) {
755  return TRUE;
756  }
757 
758  //
759  // This pool allocation is permitted, but because we're starting to run low,
760  // trigger a round of dereferencing in parallel before returning success.
761  // Note this is only done on machines with at least 1GB of RAM as smaller
762  // configuration machines will already trigger this due to physical page
763  // consumption.
764  //
765 
766  Status = TRUE;
767 
768 nopool:
769 
770  //
771  // Running low on pool - if this request is not for session pool,
772  // force unused segment trimming when appropriate.
773  //
774 
775  if ((PoolType & SESSION_POOL_MASK) == 0) {
776 
777  if ((PoolType & BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == NonPagedPool) {
778 
779  MmPreemptiveTrims[MmPreemptForNonPagedPriority] += 1;
780 
781  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
782 
783  //
784  // Only pulse the event if it is not already set. This saves
785  // on dispatcher lock contention, but more importantly since
786  // KePulse always clears the event it saves us having to check
787  // whether to set it (and potentially do the setting) afterwards.
788  //
789 
790  if (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
791  KePulseEvent (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
792  }
793 
794  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock,
795  OldIrql);
796  }
797  else {
798 
799  MmPreemptiveTrims[MmPreemptForPagedPriority] += 1;
800 
801  KeAcquireGuardedMutex (&MmPagedPoolMutex);
802 
803  //
804  // Only pulse the event if it is not already set. This saves
805  // on dispatcher lock contention, but more importantly since
806  // KePulse always clears the event it saves us having to check
807  // whether to set it (and potentially do the setting) afterwards.
808  //
809 
810  if (MiLowPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
811  KePulseEvent (MiLowPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
812  }
813 
814  KeReleaseGuardedMutex (&MmPagedPoolMutex);
815  }
816 
817  if (MI_UNUSED_SEGMENTS_SURPLUS()) {
818  KeSetEvent (&MmUnusedSegmentCleanup, 0, FALSE);
819  }
820  else {
821  MiTrimSegmentCache ();
822  }
823  }
824 
825  if (Status == FALSE) {
826 
827  //
828  // Log this failure for debugging purposes.
829  //
830 
831  if (Priority == NormalPoolPriority) {
832  Index = MmNormalPriority;
833  }
834  else {
835  Index = MmLowPriority;
836  }
837 
838  if ((PoolType & BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == NonPagedPool) {
839  MmPoolFailures[MmNonPagedPool][Index] += 1;
840  }
841  else if (PoolType & SESSION_POOL_MASK) {
842  MmPoolFailures[MmSessionPagedPool][Index] += 1;
843  MmSessionSpace->SessionPoolAllocationFailures[0] += 1;
844  }
845  else {
846  MmPoolFailures[MmPagedPool][Index] += 1;
847  }
848 
849  MmPoolFailureReasons[MmPriorityTooLow] += 1;
850  }
851 
852  return Status;
853 }

856 VOID
857 MiFreeNonPagedPool (
858  IN PVOID StartingAddress,
859  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages
860  )
861 
862 /*++
863 
864 Routine Description:
865 
866  This function releases virtually mapped nonpaged expansion pool.
867 
868 Arguments:
869 
870  StartingAddress - Supplies the starting address.
871 
872  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to free.
873 
874 Return Value:
875 
876  None.
877 
878 Environment:
879 
880  These functions are used by the internal Mm page allocation/free routines
881  only and should not be called directly.
882 
883  The nonpaged pool spinlock must be held at DISPATCH_LEVEL when calling
884  this function.
885 
886 --*/
887 
888 {
889  PFN_NUMBER i;
890  PMMPFN Pfn1;
891  PMMPTE PointerPte;
892  PFN_NUMBER ResAvailToReturn;
893  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
894 
895  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartingAddress);
896 
897  //
898  // Return commitment.
899  //
900 
901  MiReturnCommitment (NumberOfPages);
902 
903  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_NONPAGED_POOL_EXPANSION,
904  NumberOfPages);
905 
906  ResAvailToReturn = 0;
907 
908  LOCK_PFN_AT_DPC ();
909 
910  if (MiExpansionPoolPagesInUse > MiExpansionPoolPagesInitialCharge) {
911  ResAvailToReturn = MiExpansionPoolPagesInUse - MiExpansionPoolPagesInitialCharge;
912  }
913  MiExpansionPoolPagesInUse -= NumberOfPages;
914 
915  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
916 
917  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
918 
919  //
920  // Set the pointer to the PTE as empty so the page
921  // is deleted when the reference count goes to zero.
922  //
923 
924  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
925  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1);
926  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount = 0;
927  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
928 #if DBG
929  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = StandbyPageList;
930 #endif
931  MiDecrementReferenceCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
932 
933  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
934 
935  PointerPte += 1;
936  }
937 
938  //
939  // No TB flush is done here - the system PTE management code will
940  // lazily flush as needed.
941  //
942 
943  UNLOCK_PFN_FROM_DPC ();
944 
945  //
946  // Generally there is no need to update resident available
947  // pages at this time as it has all been done during initialization.
948  // However, only some of the expansion pool was charged at init, so
949  // calculate how much (if any) resident available page charge to return.
950  //
951 
952  if (ResAvailToReturn > NumberOfPages) {
953  ResAvailToReturn = NumberOfPages;
954  }
955 
956  if (ResAvailToReturn != 0) {
957  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (ResAvailToReturn, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_EXPANSION_NONPAGED_POOL);
958  }
959 
960  PointerPte -= NumberOfPages;
961 
962  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte,
963  (ULONG)NumberOfPages,
964  NonPagedPoolExpansion);
965 }

967 LOGICAL
968 MiFreeAllExpansionNonPagedPool (
969  VOID
970  )
971 
972 /*++
973 
974 Routine Description:
975 
976  This function releases all virtually mapped nonpaged expansion pool.
977 
978 Arguments:
979 
980  None.
981 
982 Return Value:
983 
984  TRUE if pages were freed, FALSE if not.
985 
986 Environment:
987 
988  Kernel mode.
989 
990 --*/
991 
992 {
993  ULONG Index;
994  KIRQL OldIrql;
995  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
996  LOGICAL FreedPool;
997  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY FreePageInfo;
998 
999  FreedPool = FALSE;
1000 
1001  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
1002 
1003  for (Index = 0; Index < MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS; Index += 1) {
1004 
1005  Entry = MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index].Flink;
1006 
1007  while (Entry != &MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index]) {
1008 
1009  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
1010  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)Entry, 0);
1011  }
1012 
1013  //
1014  // The list is not empty, see if this one is virtually
1015  // mapped.
1016  //
1017 
1018  FreePageInfo = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
1019  MMFREE_POOL_ENTRY,
1020  List);
1021 
1022  if ((!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(FreePageInfo)) &&
1023  ((PVOID)FreePageInfo >= MmNonPagedPoolExpansionStart)) {
1024 
1025  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == FALSE) {
1026  RemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
1027  }
1028  else {
1029  MiProtectedPoolRemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
1030  }
1031 
1032  MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool -= FreePageInfo->Size;
1033  ASSERT ((LONG)MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool >= 0);
1034 
1035  FreedPool = TRUE;
1036 
1037  MiFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)FreePageInfo,
1038  FreePageInfo->Size);
1039 
1040  Index = (ULONG)-1;
1041  break;
1042  }
1043 
1044  Entry = FreePageInfo->List.Flink;
1045 
1046  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
1047  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)FreePageInfo,
1048  (ULONG)FreePageInfo->Size);
1049  }
1050  }
1051  }
1052 
1053  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock, OldIrql);
1054 
1055  return FreedPool;
1056 }

1188 PVOID
1189 MiAllocatePoolPages (
1190  IN POOL_TYPE PoolType,
1191  IN SIZE_T SizeInBytes
1192  )
1193 
1194 /*++
1195 
1196 Routine Description:
1197 
1198  This function allocates a set of pages from the specified pool
1199  and returns the starting virtual address to the caller.
1200 
1201 Arguments:
1202 
1203  PoolType - Supplies the type of pool from which to obtain pages.
1204 
1205  SizeInBytes - Supplies the size of the request in bytes. The actual
1206  size returned is rounded up to a page boundary.
1207 
1208 Return Value:
1209 
1210  Returns a pointer to the allocated pool, or NULL if no more pool is
1211  available.
1212 
1213 Environment:
1214 
1215  These functions are used by the general pool allocation routines
1216  and should not be called directly.
1217 
1218  Kernel mode, IRQL at DISPATCH_LEVEL.
1219 
1220 --*/
1221 
1222 {
1223  PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages;
1224  ULONG TimeStamp;
1225  ULONG LastTimeStamp;
1226  ULONG StartPosition;
1227  ULONG EndPosition;
1228  PMMPTE StartingPte;
1229  PMMPTE PointerPte;
1230  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1231  PMMPFN PfnList;
1232  MMPTE TempPte;
1233  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1234  PVOID BaseVa;
1235  KIRQL OldIrql;
1236  PFN_NUMBER i;
1237  PFN_NUMBER j;
1238  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
1239  PLIST_ENTRY ListHead;
1240  PLIST_ENTRY LastListHead;
1241  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY FreePageInfo;
1242  PMM_SESSION_SPACE SessionSpace;
1243  PMM_PAGED_POOL_INFO PagedPoolInfo;
1244  PVOID VirtualAddress;
1245  PVOID VirtualAddressSave;
1246  ULONG_PTR Index;
1247  ULONG PageTableCount;
1248  PFN_NUMBER FreePoolInPages;
1249  LOGICAL FlushedTb;
1250  ULONG FlushCount;
1251  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
1252  LOGICAL PreviousPteNeededFlush;
1253 
1254  SizeInPages = BYTES_TO_PAGES (SizeInBytes);
1255 
1256 #if DBG
1257  if (MmCheckRequestInPages != 0) {
1258  ASSERT (SizeInPages < MmCheckRequestInPages);
1259  }
1260 #endif
1261 
1262  if ((PoolType & BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == NonPagedPool) {
1263 
1264  if ((SizeInPages == 1) &&
1265  (ExQueryDepthSList (&MiNonPagedPoolSListHead) != 0)) {
1266 
1267  BaseVa = InterlockedPopEntrySList (&MiNonPagedPoolSListHead);
1268 
1269  if (BaseVa != NULL) {
1270 
1271  if (PoolType & POOL_VERIFIER_MASK) {
1272  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(BaseVa)) {
1273  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (BaseVa);
1274  }
1275  else {
1276  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress(BaseVa);
1277  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
1278  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
1279  }
1280  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1281  Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation = 1;
1282  }
1283 
1284  return BaseVa;
1285  }
1286  }
1287 
1288  Index = SizeInPages - 1;
1289 
1290  if (Index >= MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS) {
1291  Index = MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS - 1;
1292  }
1293 
1294  //
1295  // NonPaged pool is linked together through the pages themselves.
1296  //
1297 
1298  ListHead = &MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index];
1299  LastListHead = &MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS];
1300 
1301  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
1302 
1303  do {
1304 
1305  Entry = ListHead->Flink;
1306 
1307  while (Entry != ListHead) {
1308 
1309  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
1310  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)Entry, 0);
1311  }
1312 
1313  //
1314  // The list is not empty, see if this one has enough space.
1315  //
1316 
1317  FreePageInfo = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
1318  MMFREE_POOL_ENTRY,
1319  List);
1320 
1321  ASSERT (FreePageInfo->Signature == MM_FREE_POOL_SIGNATURE);
1322  if (FreePageInfo->Size >= SizeInPages) {
1323 
1324  //
1325  // This entry has sufficient space, remove
1326  // the pages from the end of the allocation.
1327  //
1328 
1329  FreePageInfo->Size -= SizeInPages;
1330 
1331  BaseVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)FreePageInfo +
1332  (FreePageInfo->Size << PAGE_SHIFT));
1333 
1334  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == FALSE) {
1335  RemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
1336  }
1337  else {
1338  MiProtectedPoolRemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
1339  }
1340 
1341  if (FreePageInfo->Size != 0) {
1342 
1343  //
1344  // Insert any remainder into the correct list.
1345  //
1346 
1347  Index = (ULONG)(FreePageInfo->Size - 1);
1348  if (Index >= MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS) {
1349  Index = MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS - 1;
1350  }
1351 
1352  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == FALSE) {
1353  InsertTailList (&MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index],
1354  &FreePageInfo->List);
1355  }
1356  else {
1357  MiProtectedPoolInsertList (&MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index],
1358  &FreePageInfo->List,
1359  FALSE);
1360 
1361  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)FreePageInfo,
1362  (ULONG)FreePageInfo->Size);
1363  }
1364  }
1365 
1366  //
1367  // Adjust the number of free pages remaining in the pool.
1368  //
1369 
1370  MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool -= SizeInPages;
1371  ASSERT ((LONG)MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool >= 0);
1372 
1373  //
1374  // Mark start and end of allocation in the PFN database.
1375  //
1376 
1377  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(BaseVa)) {
1378 
1379  //
1380  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
1381  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
1382  //
1383 
1384  PointerPte = NULL;
1385  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (BaseVa);
1386  }
1387  else {
1388  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress(BaseVa);
1389  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
1390  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
1391  }
1392  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1393 
1394  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
1395  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
1396 
1397  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;
1398 
1399  if (PoolType & POOL_VERIFIER_MASK) {
1400  Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation = 1;
1401  }
1402 
1403  //
1404  // Calculate the ending PTE's address.
1405  //
1406 
1407  if (SizeInPages != 1) {
1408  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
1409  Pfn1 += SizeInPages - 1;
1410  }
1411  else {
1412  PointerPte += SizeInPages - 1;
1413  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
1414  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
1415  }
1416  }
1417 
1418  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0);
1419 
1420  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;
1421 
1422  MmAllocatedNonPagedPool += SizeInPages;
1423 
1424  FreePoolInPages = MmMaximumNonPagedPoolInPages - MmAllocatedNonPagedPool;
1425 
1426  if (FreePoolInPages < MiHighNonPagedPoolThreshold) {
1427 
1428  //
1429  // Read the state directly instead of calling
1430  // KeReadStateEvent since we are holding the nonpaged
1431  // pool lock and want to keep instructions at a
1432  // minimum.
1433  //
1434 
1435  if (MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState != 0) {
1436  KeClearEvent (MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent);
1437  }
1438  if (FreePoolInPages <= MiLowNonPagedPoolThreshold) {
1439  if (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
1440  KeSetEvent (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
1441  }
1442  }
1443  }
1444 
1445  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock,
1446  OldIrql);
1447 
1448  return BaseVa;
1449  }
1450 
1451  Entry = FreePageInfo->List.Flink;
1452 
1453  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
1454  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)FreePageInfo,
1455  (ULONG)FreePageInfo->Size);
1456  }
1457  }
1458 
1459  ListHead += 1;
1460 
1461  } while (ListHead < LastListHead);
1462 
1463  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock, OldIrql);
1464 
1465  //
1466  // No more entries on the list, expand nonpaged pool if
1467  // possible to satisfy this request.
1468  //
1469  // If pool is starting to run low then free some page cache up now.
1470  // While this can never guarantee pool allocations will succeed,
1471  // it does give allocators a better chance.
1472  //
1473 
1474  FreePoolInPages = MmMaximumNonPagedPoolInPages - MmAllocatedNonPagedPool;
1475  if (FreePoolInPages < (3 * 1024 * 1024) / PAGE_SIZE) {
1476  MmPreemptiveTrims[MmPreemptForNonPaged] += 1;
1477  MiTrimSegmentCache ();
1478  }
1479 
1480 #if defined (_WIN64)
1481  if (SizeInPages >= _4gb) {
1482  return NULL;
1483  }
1484 #endif
1485 
1486  //
1487  // Try to find system PTEs to expand the pool into.
1488  //
1489 
1490  StartingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes ((ULONG)SizeInPages,
1491  NonPagedPoolExpansion);
1492 
1493  if (StartingPte == NULL) {
1494 
1495  //
1496  // There are no free physical PTEs to expand nonpaged pool.
1497  //
1498  // Check to see if there are too many unused segments lying
1499  // around. If so, set an event so they get deleted.
1500  //
1501 
1502  if (MI_UNUSED_SEGMENTS_SURPLUS()) {
1503  KeSetEvent (&MmUnusedSegmentCleanup, 0, FALSE);
1504  }
1505 
1506  //
1507  // If there are any cached expansion PTEs, free them now in
1508  // an attempt to get enough contiguous VA for our caller.
1509  //
1510 
1511  if ((SizeInPages > 1) && (MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool != 0)) {
1512 
1513  if (MiFreeAllExpansionNonPagedPool () == TRUE) {
1514 
1515  StartingPte = MiReserveSystemPtes ((ULONG)SizeInPages,
1516  NonPagedPoolExpansion);
1517  }
1518  }
1519 
1520  if (StartingPte == NULL) {
1521 
1522  MmPoolFailures[MmNonPagedPool][MmHighPriority] += 1;
1523  MmPoolFailureReasons[MmNonPagedNoPtes] += 1;
1524 
1525  //
1526  // Running low on pool - force unused segment trimming.
1527  //
1528 
1529  MiTrimSegmentCache ();
1530 
1531  return NULL;
1532  }
1533  }
1534 
1535  //
1536  // See if the allocation can be satisfied from expansion slush ...
1537  //
1538 
1539  PfnList = NULL;
1540 
1541  if (MiCachedNonPagedPoolCount >= SizeInPages) {
1542 
1543  i = SizeInPages;
1544 
1545  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
1546 
1547  if (MiCachedNonPagedPoolCount >= i) {
1548  Pfn1 = MiCachedNonPagedPool;
1549  PfnList = Pfn1;
1550  do {
1551  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid);
1552  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1);
1553  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1);
1554  ASSERT (Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long == MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE);
1555  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.MustBeCached == 1);
1556 
1557  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid);
1558 
1559  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
1560  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
1561 
1562  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached);
1563  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) Pfn1->u1.Event;
1564  i -= 1;
1565  } while (i != 0);
1566 
1567  MiCachedNonPagedPool = Pfn1;
1568  MiCachedNonPagedPoolCount -= SizeInPages;
1569 #if DBG
1570  if (MiCachedNonPagedPoolCount == 0) {
1571  ASSERT (MiCachedNonPagedPool == NULL);
1572  }
1573 #endif
1574  }
1575 
1576  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
1577  }
1578 
1579  //
1580  // Charge commitment as nonpaged pool uses physical memory.
1581  //
1582 
1583  if ((PfnList == NULL) &&
1584  (MiChargeCommitmentCantExpand (SizeInPages, FALSE) == FALSE)) {
1585 
1586  if ((PsGetCurrentThread()->MemoryMaker == 1) &&
1587  (!KeIsExecutingDpc ())) {
1588 
1589  MiChargeCommitmentCantExpand (SizeInPages, TRUE);
1590  }
1591  else {
1592  MiReleaseSystemPtes (StartingPte,
1593  (ULONG)SizeInPages,
1594  NonPagedPoolExpansion);
1595 
1596  MmPoolFailures[MmNonPagedPool][MmHighPriority] += 1;
1597  MmPoolFailureReasons[MmNonPagedNoCommit] += 1;
1598  MiTrimSegmentCache ();
1599  return NULL;
1600  }
1601  }
1602 
1603  PointerPte = StartingPte;
1604  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
1605  i = SizeInPages;
1606 
1607  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
1608 
1609  if (PfnList != NULL) {
1610  Pfn1 = PfnList;
1611  ASSERT (PfnList->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
1612  ASSERT (PfnList->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
1613  PfnList->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;
1614  if (PoolType & POOL_VERIFIER_MASK) {
1615  PfnList->u4.VerifierAllocation = 1;
1616  }
1617 
1618  //
1619  // The lock must be acquired prior to filling any PTEs to
1620  // prevent a free happening in parallel from mistakenly trying
1621  // to coalesce with this allocation !
1622  //
1623 
1624  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
1625 
1626  do {
1627 
1628  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1);
1629  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1);
1630  ASSERT (Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long == MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE);
1631  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.MustBeCached == 1);
1632  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0) ||

2301  if (MiHighPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState != 0) {
2302  KeClearEvent (MiHighPagedPoolEvent);
2303  }
2304  if (FreePoolInPages <= MiLowPagedPoolThreshold) {
2305  if (MiLowPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
2306  KeSetEvent (MiLowPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
2307  }
2308  }
2309  }
2310 
2311  KeReleaseGuardedMutex (&MmPagedPoolMutex);
2312  InterlockedExchangeAdd ((PLONG) &MmPagedPoolCommit, (LONG)SizeInPages);
2313  BaseVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR) MmPagedPoolStart +
2314  ((ULONG_PTR)StartPosition << PAGE_SHIFT));
2315  }
2316 
2317  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&PagedPoolInfo->PagedPoolCommit,
2318  SizeInPages);
2319 
2320  //
2321  // Carefully check the TB flush time stamps to decide if a flush is needed.
2322  //
2323 
2324  FlushCount = 0;
2325  LastTimeStamp = 0;
2326  PreviousPteNeededFlush = FALSE;
2327  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseVa);
2328 
2329  for (i = 0; i < SizeInPages; i += 1, PointerPte += 1) {
2330  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
2331 
2332  TimeStamp = (ULONG) PointerPte->u.Soft.PageFileHigh;
2333 
2334  if (TimeStamp == 0) {
2335 
2336  //
2337  // This entry has already been flushed.
2338  //
2339 
2340  PreviousPteNeededFlush = FALSE;
2341  LastTimeStamp = TimeStamp;
2342  continue;
2343  }
2344 
2345  if (TimeStamp == LastTimeStamp) {
2346 
2347  if (PreviousPteNeededFlush == TRUE) {
2348 
2349  //
2350  // If this entry is the same as the prior one then it must be
2351  // treated the same with respect to flushes.
2352  //
2353 
2354  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2355  FlushCount += 1;
2356  if (FlushCount == MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
2357  FlushCount = 0;
2358  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x1E);
2359  break;
2360  }
2361  }
2362 
2363  continue;
2364  }
2365 
2366  if (MiCompareTbFlushTimeStamp (TimeStamp, MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
2367 
2368  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2369  FlushCount += 1;
2370  if (FlushCount == MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
2371  FlushCount = 0;
2372  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x1E);
2373  break;
2374  }
2375  PreviousPteNeededFlush = TRUE;
2376  }
2377  else {
2378  PreviousPteNeededFlush = FALSE;
2379  }
2380 
2381  LastTimeStamp = TimeStamp;
2382  }
2383 
2384  //
2385  // Flush the TB entries for any relevant pages.
2386  //
2387 
2388  if (FlushCount == 0) {
2389  NOTHING;
2390  }
2391  else if (FlushCount == 1) {
2392  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
2393  }
2394  else {
2395  ASSERT (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT);
2396  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
2397  }
2398 
2399  TempPte.u.Long = MM_KERNEL_DEMAND_ZERO_PTE;
2400 
2401  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_INVALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
2402 
2403  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseVa);
2404 
2405  StartingPte = PointerPte + SizeInPages;
2406 
2407  //
2408  // Fill the PTEs inline instead of using MiFillMemoryPte because on
2409  // most platforms MiFillMemoryPte degrades to a function call and
2410  // typically only a small number of PTEs are filled here.
2411  //
2412 
2413  do {
2414  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
2415  PointerPte += 1;
2416  } while (PointerPte < StartingPte);
2417 
2418  return BaseVa;
2419 }
2420 
2421 ULONG
2422 MiFreePoolPages (
2423  IN PVOID StartingAddress
2424  )
2425 
2426 /*++
2427 
2428 Routine Description:
2429 
2430  This function returns a set of pages back to the pool from
2431  which they were obtained. Once the pages have been deallocated
2432  the region provided by the allocation becomes available for
2433  allocation to other callers, i.e. any data in the region is now
2434  trashed and cannot be referenced.
2435 
2436 Arguments:
2437 
2438  StartingAddress - Supplies the starting address which was returned
2439  in a previous call to MiAllocatePoolPages.
2440 
2441 Return Value:
2442 
2443  Returns the number of pages deallocated.
2444 
2445 Environment:
2446 
2447  These functions are used by the general pool allocation routines
2448  and should not be called directly.
2449 
2450 --*/
2451 
2452 {
2453  PMMPFN PfnList;
2454  KIRQL OldIrql;
2455  KIRQL PfnIrql;
2456  ULONG StartPosition;
2457  ULONG Index;
2458  PFN_NUMBER i;
2459  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
2460  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
2461  PMMPTE PointerPte;
2462  PMMPTE StartPte;
2463  PMMPFN Pfn1;
2464  PMMPFN StartPfn;
2465  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY Entry;
2466  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY NextEntry;
2467  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY LastEntry;
2468  PMM_PAGED_POOL_INFO PagedPoolInfo;
2469  PMM_SESSION_SPACE SessionSpace;
2470  PFN_NUMBER PagesFreed;
2471  MMPFNENTRY OriginalPfnFlags;
2472  ULONG_PTR VerifierAllocation;
2473  PULONG BitMap;
2474  PKGUARDED_MUTEX PoolMutex;
2475  PFN_NUMBER FreePoolInPages;
2476 #if DBG

2478  PMMPFN DebugPfn;
2479  PMMPFN LastDebugPfn;
2480 #endif
2481 
2482  //
2483  // Determine pool type based on the virtual address of the block
2484  // to deallocate.
2485  //
2486  // This assumes paged pool is virtually contiguous.
2487  //
2488 
2489  if ((StartingAddress >= MmPagedPoolStart) &&
2490  (StartingAddress <= MmPagedPoolEnd)) {
2491  SessionSpace = NULL;
2492  PagedPoolInfo = &MmPagedPoolInfo;
2493  StartPosition = (ULONG)(((PCHAR)StartingAddress -
2494  (PCHAR)MmPagedPoolStart) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
2495  PoolMutex = &MmPagedPoolMutex;
2496  }
2497  else if (MI_IS_SESSION_POOL_ADDRESS (StartingAddress) == TRUE) {
2498  SessionSpace = SESSION_GLOBAL (MmSessionSpace);
2499  ASSERT (SessionSpace);
2500  PagedPoolInfo = &SessionSpace->PagedPoolInfo;
2501  StartPosition = (ULONG)(((PCHAR)StartingAddress -
2502  (PCHAR)SessionSpace->PagedPoolStart) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
2503  PoolMutex = &SessionSpace->PagedPoolMutex;
2504  }
2505  else {
2506 
2507  if (StartingAddress < MM_SYSTEM_RANGE_START) {
2508  KeBugCheckEx (BAD_POOL_CALLER,
2509  0x40,
2510  (ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress,
2511  (ULONG_PTR)MM_SYSTEM_RANGE_START,
2512  0);
2513  }
2514 
2515  StartPosition = (ULONG)(((PCHAR)StartingAddress -
2516  (PCHAR) MmNonPagedPoolStart) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
2517 
2518  //
2519  // Check to ensure this page is really the start of an allocation.
2520  //
2521 
2522  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (StartingAddress)) {
2523 
2524  //
2525  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
2526  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
2527  //
2528 
2529  PointerPte = NULL;
2530  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (StartingAddress));
2531  ASSERT (StartPosition < (ULONG) BYTES_TO_PAGES (MmSizeOfNonPagedPoolInBytes));
2532 
2533  if ((StartingAddress < MmNonPagedPoolStart) ||
2534  (StartingAddress >= MmNonPagedPoolEnd0)) {
2535  KeBugCheckEx (BAD_POOL_CALLER,
2536  0x42,
2537  (ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress,
2538  0,
2539  0);
2540  }
2541  }
2542  else {
2543  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartingAddress);
2544 
2545  if (((StartingAddress >= MmNonPagedPoolExpansionStart) &&
2546  (StartingAddress < MmNonPagedPoolEnd)) ||
2547  ((StartingAddress >= MmNonPagedPoolStart) &&
2548  (StartingAddress < MmNonPagedPoolEnd0))) {
2549  NOTHING;
2550  }
2551  else {
2552  KeBugCheckEx (BAD_POOL_CALLER,
2553  0x43,
2554  (ULONG_PTR)StartingAddress,
2555  0,
2556  0);
2557  }
2558  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2559  }
2560 
2561  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0) {
2562  KeBugCheckEx (BAD_POOL_CALLER,
2563  0x41,
2564  (ULONG_PTR) StartingAddress,
2565  (ULONG_PTR) MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (Pfn1),
2566  MmHighestPhysicalPage);
2567  }
2568 
2569  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame != MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME);
2570

2572  // Hang single page allocations off our slist header.
2573  //
2574

2576  (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0) &&
2577  (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0) &&
2578  (ExQueryDepthSList (&MiNonPagedPoolSListHead) < MiNonPagedPoolSListMaximum)) {
2579  InterlockedPushEntrySList (&MiNonPagedPoolSListHead,
2580  (PSLIST_ENTRY) StartingAddress);
2581  return 1;
2582  }

2585  // The nonpaged pool being freed may be the target of a delayed unlock.
2586  // Since these pages may be immediately released, force any pending
2587  // delayed actions to occur now.
2588  //
2589 
2590 #if !defined(MI_MULTINODE)
2591  if (MmPfnDeferredList != NULL) {
2592  MiDeferredUnlockPages (0);
2593  }
2594 #else
2595  //
2596  // Each and every node's deferred list would have to be checked so
2597  // we might as well go the long way and just call.
2598  //
2599 
2600  MiDeferredUnlockPages (0);
2601 #endif
2602

2604 
2605  OriginalPfnFlags = Pfn1->u3.e1;
2606  VerifierAllocation = Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation;
2607 
2608  //
2609  // ASSERT to ensure the pool being freed is not still in use
2610  // for an I/O.
2611  //
2612 
2613  if ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) ||
2614  ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount > 1) &&
2615  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0))) {
2616 
2617  MiBadRefCount (Pfn1);
2618  }
2619 
2620  //
2621  // Find end of allocation and release the pages.
2622  //
2623 
2624  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2625  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (StartPte = NULL);
2626  while (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0) {
2627  Pfn1 += 1;
2628 
2629  //
2630  // ASSERT to ensure the pool being freed is not still in use
2631  // for an I/O.
2632  //
2633 
2634  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
2635  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1) ||
2636  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 1));
2637  }
2638  NumberOfPages = Pfn1 - StartPfn + 1;
2639  }
2640  else {
2641  StartPte = PointerPte;
2642  while (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0) {
2643  PointerPte += 1;
2644  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2645 
2646  //
2647  // ASSERT to ensure the pool being freed is not still in use
2648  // for an I/O.
2649  //
2650 
2651  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
2652  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1) ||
2653  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 1));
2654  }
2655  NumberOfPages = PointerPte - StartPte + 1;
2656  }
2657 
2658  if (VerifierAllocation != 0) {
2659  VerifierFreeTrackedPool (StartingAddress,
2660  NumberOfPages << PAGE_SHIFT,
2661  NonPagedPool,
2662  FALSE);
2663  }
2664 
2665 #if DBG
2666  if (MiFillFreedPool != 0) {
2667  RtlFillMemoryUlong (StartingAddress,
2668  PAGE_SIZE * NumberOfPages,
2669  MiFillFreedPool);
2670  }
2671 #endif
2672 
2673  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
2674 
2675  StartPfn->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 0;
2676  StartPfn->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation = 0;
2677  StartPfn->u4.VerifierAllocation = 0;
2678 
2679  MmAllocatedNonPagedPool -= NumberOfPages;
2680 
2681  FreePoolInPages = MmMaximumNonPagedPoolInPages - MmAllocatedNonPagedPool;
2682 
2683  if (FreePoolInPages > MiLowNonPagedPoolThreshold) {
2684 
2685  //
2686  // Read the state directly instead of calling
2687  // KeReadStateEvent since we are holding the nonpaged
2688  // pool lock and want to keep instructions at a
2689  // minimum.
2690  //
2691

2693  KeClearEvent (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent);
2694  }
2695  if (FreePoolInPages >= MiHighNonPagedPoolThreshold) {
2696  if (MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
2697  KeSetEvent (MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
2698  }
2699  }
2700  }
2701 
2702  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 0;
2703 
2704  if (StartingAddress >= MmNonPagedPoolExpansionStart) {
2705 
2706  //
2707  // This page was from the expanded pool, should
2708  // it be freed?
2709  //
2710  // NOTE: all pages in the expanded pool area have PTEs
2711  // so no physical address checks need to be performed.
2712  //
2713 
2714  if (Pfn1->u4.MustBeCached == 1) {
2715 
2716  //
2717  // This is a slush page that is concurrently mapped
2718  // (cached) within the kernel or HAL's large page mapping.
2719  // To prevent a possible TB attribute conflict, these pages
2720  // are never put on the general purpose page free lists.
2721  // Instead they are cached here for nonpaged pool usage only.
2722  //
2723

2725  PointerPte = StartPte;

2727  //
2728  // Hold the nonpaged pool lock until all the PTEs are cleared
2729  // so another thread trying to coalesce will see consistent
2730  // values.
2731  //
2732 
2733  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1, PointerPte += 1) {
2734 
2735  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
2736  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
2737  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2738 
2739  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid);
2740  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute == MiCached);
2741 
2742  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 1);
2743  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1);
2744  ASSERT (Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long == MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE);
2745  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.MustBeCached == 1);
2746  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
2747  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0);
2748  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
2749  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
2750

2752  PfnList = Pfn1;
2753  }

2756  StartPfn->u1.Event = (PKEVENT) MiCachedNonPagedPool;
2757  MiCachedNonPagedPool = PfnList;
2758  MiCachedNonPagedPoolCount += NumberOfPages;
2759  UNLOCK_PFN2 (PfnIrql);
2760 
2761  MiReleaseSystemPtes (StartPte,
2762  (ULONG)NumberOfPages,
2763  NonPagedPoolExpansion);
2764 
2765  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock, OldIrql);
2766 
2767  //
2768  // No TB flush is done here - the system PTE management code
2769  // will lazily flush as needed.
2770  //
2771 
2772  return (ULONG)NumberOfPages;
2773  }
2774

2776  (MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool > MmFreedExpansionPoolMaximum) ||

2778  (MiExpansionPoolPagesInUse > MiExpansionPoolPagesInitialCharge))) {
2779 
2780  //
2781  // Free these pages back to the free page list.
2782  //
2783 
2784  MiFreeNonPagedPool (StartingAddress, NumberOfPages);
2785 
2786  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock, OldIrql);
2787 
2788  return (ULONG)NumberOfPages;
2789  }
2790  }
2791 
2792  //
2793  // Add the pages to the list of free pages.
2794  //
2795 
2796  MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool += NumberOfPages;
2797 
2798  //
2799  // Check to see if the next allocation is free.
2800  // We cannot walk off the end of nonpaged expansion
2801  // pages as the highest expansion allocation is always
2802  // virtual and guard-paged.
2803  //
2804 
2805  i = NumberOfPages;
2806 
2807  ASSERT (MiEndOfInitialPoolFrame != 0);
2808 
2809  if (MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (Pfn1) == MiEndOfInitialPoolFrame) {
2810  PointerPte += 1;
2811  Pfn1 = NULL;
2812  }
2813  else if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2814  Pfn1 += 1;
2815  ASSERT ((PCHAR)StartingAddress + NumberOfPages < (PCHAR)MmNonPagedPoolStart + MmSizeOfNonPagedPoolInBytes);
2816  }
2817  else {
2818  PointerPte += 1;
2819  ASSERT ((PCHAR)StartingAddress + NumberOfPages <= (PCHAR)MmNonPagedPoolEnd);
2820 
2821  //
2822  // Unprotect the previously freed pool so it can be merged.
2823  //
2824 
2825  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
2826  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool (
2827  (PVOID)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte),
2828  0);
2829  }
2830 
2831  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
2832  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2833  }
2834  else {
2835  Pfn1 = NULL;
2836  }
2837  }
2838 
2839  if ((Pfn1 != NULL) && (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0)) {
2840 
2841  //
2842  // This range of pages is free. Remove this entry
2843  // from the list and add these pages to the current
2844  // range being freed.
2845  //
2846 
2847  Entry = (PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY)((PCHAR)StartingAddress
2848  + (NumberOfPages << PAGE_SHIFT));
2849  ASSERT (Entry->Signature == MM_FREE_POOL_SIGNATURE);
2850  ASSERT (Entry->Owner == Entry);
2851 
2852 #if DBG
2853  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2854 
2855  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(StartingAddress));
2856 
2857  //
2858  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
2859  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
2860  //
2861 
2862  DebugPfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (Entry));
2863  DebugPfn += Entry->Size;
2864  if (MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (DebugPfn - 1) != MiEndOfInitialPoolFrame) {
2865  ASSERT (DebugPfn->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 1);
2866  }
2867  }
2868  else {
2869  DebugPte = PointerPte + Entry->Size;
2870  if ((DebugPte-1)->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
2871  DebugPfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT ((DebugPte-1)->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2872  if (MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (DebugPfn) != MiEndOfInitialPoolFrame) {
2873  if (DebugPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
2874  DebugPfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (DebugPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2875  ASSERT (DebugPfn->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 1);
2876  }
2877  }
2878 
2879  }
2880  }
2881 #endif
2882 
2883  i += Entry->Size;
2884  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == FALSE) {
2885  RemoveEntryList (&Entry->List);
2886  }
2887  else {
2888  MiProtectedPoolRemoveEntryList (&Entry->List);
2889  }
2890  }
2891 
2892  //
2893  // Check to see if the previous page is the end of an allocation.
2894  // If it is not the end of an allocation, it must be free and
2895  // therefore this allocation can be tagged onto the end of
2896  // that allocation.
2897  //
2898  // We cannot walk off the beginning of expansion pool because it is
2899  // guard-paged. If the initial pool is superpaged instead, we are also
2900  // safe as the must succeed pages always have EndOfAllocation set.
2901  //
2902 
2903  Entry = (PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY)StartingAddress;
2904 
2905  ASSERT (MiStartOfInitialPoolFrame != 0);
2906 
2907  if (MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (StartPfn) == MiStartOfInitialPoolFrame) {
2908  Pfn1 = NULL;
2909  }
2910  else if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2911  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(StartingAddress));
2912  ASSERT (StartingAddress != MmNonPagedPoolStart);
2913 
2914  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (
2915  (PVOID)((PCHAR)Entry - PAGE_SIZE)));
2916 
2917  }
2918  else {
2919  PointerPte -= NumberOfPages + 1;
2920 
2921  //
2922  // Unprotect the previously freed pool so it can be merged.
2923  //
2924 
2925  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
2926  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool (
2927  (PVOID)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPte),
2928  0);
2929  }
2930 
2931  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
2932  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
2933  }
2934  else {
2935  Pfn1 = NULL;
2936  }
2937  }
2938  if (Pfn1 != NULL) {
2939  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0) {
2940 
2941  //
2942  // This range of pages is free, add these pages to
2943  // this entry. The owner field points to the address
2944  // of the list entry which is linked into the free pool
2945  // pages list.
2946  //
2947 
2948  Entry = (PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY)((PCHAR)StartingAddress - PAGE_SIZE);
2949  ASSERT (Entry->Signature == MM_FREE_POOL_SIGNATURE);
2950  Entry = Entry->Owner;
2951 
2952  //
2953  // Unprotect the previously freed pool so we can merge it
2954  //
2955 
2956  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
2957  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)Entry, 0);
2958  }
2959 
2960  //
2961  // If this entry became larger than MM_SMALL_ALLOCATIONS
2962  // pages, move it to the tail of the list. This keeps the
2963  // small allocations at the front of the list.

3676  Ensure that the current session has no pool allocations since it is about
3677  to exit. All session allocations must be freed prior to session exit.
3678 
3679 Arguments:
3680 
3681  None.
3682 
3683 Return Value:
3684 
3685  None.
3686 
3687 Environment:
3688 
3689  Kernel mode.
3690 
3691 --*/
3692 
3693 {
3694  SIZE_T i;
3695  ULONG PagedAllocations;
3696  ULONG NonPagedAllocations;
3697  SIZE_T PagedBytes;
3698  SIZE_T NonPagedBytes;
3699  PMMPTE StartPde;
3700  PMMPTE EndPde;
3701  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3702  MMPTE TempPte;
3703  PVOID VirtualAddress;
3704  PPOOL_TRACKER_TABLE TrackTable;
3705  PPOOL_TRACKER_TABLE TrackTableBase;
3706  SIZE_T NumberOfEntries;
3707 
3708  PAGED_CODE();
3709 
3710  TrackTableBase = MiSessionPoolTrackTable ();
3711  NumberOfEntries = MiSessionPoolTrackTableSize ();
3712 
3713  //
3714  // Note the session pool descriptor TotalPages field is not reliable
3715  // for leak checking because of the fact that nonpaged session allocations
3716  // are converted to global session allocations - thus when a small nonpaged
3717  // session allocation results in splitting a full page, the global
3718  // nonpaged pool descriptor (not the session pool descriptor) is (and must
3719  // be because of the remaining fragment) charged.
3720  //
3721 
3722  //
3723  // Make sure all the pool tracking entries are zeroed out.
3724  //
3725 
3726  PagedAllocations = 0;
3727  NonPagedAllocations = 0;
3728  PagedBytes = 0;
3729  NonPagedBytes = 0;
3730 
3731  TrackTable = TrackTableBase;
3732 
3733  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfEntries; i += 1) {
3734 
3735  PagedBytes += TrackTable->PagedBytes;
3736  NonPagedBytes += TrackTable->NonPagedBytes;
3737 
3738  PagedAllocations += (TrackTable->PagedAllocs - TrackTable->PagedFrees);
3739  NonPagedAllocations += (TrackTable->NonPagedAllocs - TrackTable->NonPagedFrees);
3740 
3741  TrackTable += 1;
3742  }
3743 
3744  if (PagedBytes != 0) {
3745 
3746  //
3747  // All page tables for this session's paged pool must be freed by now.
3748  // Being here means they aren't - this is fatal. Force in any valid
3749  // pages so that a debugger can show who the guilty party is.
3750  //
3751 
3752  StartPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmSessionSpace->PagedPoolStart);
3753  EndPde = MiGetPdeAddress (MmSessionSpace->PagedPoolEnd);
3754 
3755  while (StartPde <= EndPde) {
3756 
3757  if (StartPde->u.Long != 0) {
3758 
3759  //
3760  // Hunt through the page table page for valid pages and force
3761  // them in. Note this also forces in the page table page if
3762  // it is not already.
3763  //
3764 
3765  PointerPte = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (StartPde);
3766 
3767  for (i = 0; i < PTE_PER_PAGE; i += 1) {
3768  TempPte = *PointerPte;
3769 
3770  if ((TempPte.u.Hard.Valid == 0) &&
3771  (TempPte.u.Soft.Protection != 0) &&
3772  (TempPte.u.Soft.Protection != MM_NOACCESS)) {
3773 
3774  VirtualAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
3775  *(volatile UCHAR *)VirtualAddress = *(volatile UCHAR *)VirtualAddress;
3776 
3777  }
3778  PointerPte += 1;
3779  }
3780 
3781  }
3782 
3783  StartPde += 1;
3784  }
3785  }
3786 
3787  if ((NonPagedBytes != 0) || (PagedBytes != 0)) {
3788 
3789  KeBugCheckEx (SESSION_HAS_VALID_POOL_ON_EXIT,
3790  (ULONG_PTR)MmSessionSpace->SessionId,
3791  PagedBytes,
3792  NonPagedBytes,
3793 #if defined (_WIN64)
3794  (((ULONG_PTR) NonPagedAllocations) << 32) | (PagedAllocations)
3795 #else
3796  (NonPagedAllocations << 16) | (PagedAllocations)
3797 #endif
3798  );
3799  }
3800 
3801 #if DBG
3802 
3803  TrackTable = TrackTableBase;
3804 
3805  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfEntries; i += 1) {
3806 
3807  ASSERT (TrackTable->NonPagedBytes == 0);
3808  ASSERT (TrackTable->PagedBytes == 0);
3809  ASSERT (TrackTable->NonPagedAllocs == TrackTable->NonPagedFrees);
3810  ASSERT (TrackTable->PagedAllocs == TrackTable->PagedFrees);
3811 
3812  if (TrackTable->Key == 0) {
3813  ASSERT (TrackTable->NonPagedAllocs == 0);
3814  ASSERT (TrackTable->PagedAllocs == 0);
3815  }
3816 
3817  TrackTable += 1;
3818  }
3819 
3820  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->PagedPool.TotalPages == 0);
3821  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->PagedPool.TotalBigPages == 0);
3822  ASSERT (MmSessionSpace->PagedPool.RunningAllocs ==
3823  MmSessionSpace->PagedPool.RunningDeAllocs);
3824 #endif
3825 }

3833  )

3836

3838 
3839  Nonpaged wrapper to allocate, initialize and charge for a new page.
3840 
3841 Arguments:
3842

3844

3848  directory page which contains this PDE.
3849

3851  FALSE otherwise.

3854 
3855  Status of the page initialization.
3856

3859 {
3860  MMPTE TempPte;
3861  KIRQL OldIrql;
3862 
3863  if (SessionAllocation == TRUE) {
3864  TempPte = ValidKernelPdeLocal;
3865  }
3866  else {
3867  TempPte = ValidKernelPde;
3868  }
3869 
3870  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3871 
3872  if ((MmAvailablePages < MM_MEDIUM_LIMIT) ||
3873  (MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE() <= 1)) {
3874

3877  }

3881  // then return STATUS_RETRY so the caller knows to try again.
3882  //
3883 
3884  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
3885  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3886  return STATUS_RETRY;
3887  }
3888

3890

3892  // Allocate and map in the page at the requested address.
3893  //
3894 
3895  *PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPage (MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_PTE (PointerPde));
3896  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = *PageFrameIndex;
3897  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPde, TempPte);
3898 
3899  MiInitializePfnForOtherProcess (*PageFrameIndex,
3900  PointerPde,
3901  ContainingPageFrame);
3902 
3903  //
3904  // This page will be locked into working set and assigned an index when
3905  // the working set is set up on return.
3906  //
3907 
3908  ASSERT (MI_PFN_ELEMENT(*PageFrameIndex)->u1.WsIndex == 0);
3909 
3910  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3911 
3912  return STATUS_SUCCESS;

4252 PVOID
4253 MiFindContiguousMemoryInPool (
4254  IN PFN_NUMBER LowestPfn,
4255  IN PFN_NUMBER HighestPfn,
4256  IN PFN_NUMBER BoundaryPfn,
4257  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages,
4258  IN PVOID CallingAddress
4259  )
4260 
4261 /*++
4262 
4263 Routine Description:
4264 
4265  This function searches nonpaged pool for contiguous pages to satisfy the
4266  request. Note the pool address returned maps these pages as MmCached.
4267 
4268 Arguments:
4269 
4270  LowestPfn - Supplies the lowest acceptable physical page number.
4271 
4272  HighestPfn - Supplies the highest acceptable physical page number.
4273 
4274  BoundaryPfn - Supplies the page frame number multiple the allocation must
4275  not cross. 0 indicates it can cross any boundary.
4276 
4277  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to allocate.
4278 
4279  CallingAddress - Supplies the calling address of the allocator.
4280 
4281 Return Value:
4282 
4283  NULL - a contiguous range could not be found to satisfy the request.
4284 
4285  NON-NULL - Returns a pointer (virtual address in the nonpaged portion
4286  of the system) to the allocated physically contiguous
4287  memory.
4288 
4289 Environment:
4290 
4291  Kernel mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
4292 
4293 --*/
4294 {
4295  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4296  PMMPFN Pfn1;
4297  PVOID BaseAddress;
4298  PVOID BaseAddress2;
4299  KIRQL OldIrql;
4300  PMMFREE_POOL_ENTRY FreePageInfo;
4301  PLIST_ENTRY Entry;
4302  ULONG Index;
4303  PFN_NUMBER BoundaryMask;
4304  ULONG AllocationPosition;
4305  PVOID Va;
4306  PFN_NUMBER SpanInPages;
4307  PFN_NUMBER SpanInPages2;
4308  PFN_NUMBER FreePoolInPages;
4309 
4310  PAGED_CODE ();
4311 
4312  //
4313  // Initializing SpanInPages* is not needed for correctness
4314  // but without it the compiler cannot compile this code
4315  // W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
4316  //
4317 
4318  SpanInPages = 0;
4319  SpanInPages2 = 0;
4320 
4321  BaseAddress = NULL;
4322 
4323  BoundaryMask = ~(BoundaryPfn - 1);
4324 
4325  //
4326  // A suitable pool page was not allocated via the pool allocator.
4327  // Grab the pool lock and manually search for a page which meets
4328  // the requirements.
4329  //
4330 
4331  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
4332 
4333  //
4334  // Trace through the page allocator's pool headers for a page which
4335  // meets the requirements.
4336  //
4337  // NonPaged pool is linked together through the pages themselves.
4338  //
4339 
4340  Index = (ULONG)(SizeInPages - 1);
4341 
4342  if (Index >= MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS) {
4343  Index = MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS - 1;
4344  }
4345 
4346  OldIrql = KeAcquireQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock);
4347 
4348  while (Index < MI_MAX_FREE_LIST_HEADS) {
4349 
4350  Entry = MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index].Flink;
4351 
4352  while (Entry != &MmNonPagedPoolFreeListHead[Index]) {
4353 
4354  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
4355  MiUnProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)Entry, 0);
4356  }
4357 
4358  //
4359  // The list is not empty, see if this one meets the physical
4360  // requirements.
4361  //
4362 
4363  FreePageInfo = CONTAINING_RECORD(Entry,
4364  MMFREE_POOL_ENTRY,
4365  List);
4366 
4367  ASSERT (FreePageInfo->Signature == MM_FREE_POOL_SIGNATURE);
4368  if (FreePageInfo->Size >= SizeInPages) {
4369 
4370  //
4371  // This entry has sufficient space, check to see if the
4372  // pages meet the physical requirements.
4373  //
4374 
4375  Va = MiCheckForContiguousMemory (PAGE_ALIGN(Entry),
4376  FreePageInfo->Size,
4377  SizeInPages,
4378  LowestPfn,
4379  HighestPfn,
4380  BoundaryPfn,
4381  MiCached);
4382 
4383  if (Va != NULL) {
4384 
4385  //
4386  // These pages meet the requirements. The returned
4387  // address may butt up on the end, the front or be
4388  // somewhere in the middle. Split the Entry based
4389  // on which case it is.
4390  //
4391 
4392  Entry = PAGE_ALIGN(Entry);
4393  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == FALSE) {
4394  RemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
4395  }
4396  else {
4397  MiProtectedPoolRemoveEntryList (&FreePageInfo->List);
4398  }
4399 
4400  //
4401  // Adjust the number of free pages remaining in the pool.
4402  // The TotalBigPages calculation appears incorrect for the
4403  // case where we're splitting a block, but it's done this
4404  // way because ExFreePool corrects it when we free the
4405  // fragment block below. Likewise for
4406  // MmAllocatedNonPagedPool and MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool
4407  // which is corrected by MiFreePoolPages for the fragment.
4408  //
4409 
4410  InterlockedExchangeAdd ((PLONG)&NonPagedPoolDescriptor.TotalBigPages,
4411  (LONG)FreePageInfo->Size);
4412 
4413  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&NonPagedPoolDescriptor.TotalBytes,

4419

4421 
4422  //

4424  // KeReadStateEvent since we are holding the nonpaged
4425  // pool lock and want to keep instructions at a
4426  // minimum.
4427  //
4428

4430  KeClearEvent (MiHighNonPagedPoolEvent);
4431  }
4432  if (FreePoolInPages <= MiLowNonPagedPoolThreshold) {
4433  if (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent->Header.SignalState == 0) {
4434  KeSetEvent (MiLowNonPagedPoolEvent, 0, FALSE);
4435  }
4436  }
4437  }

4440 
4441  ASSERT ((LONG)MmNumberOfFreeNonPagedPool >= 0);
4442

4444 
4445  //
4446  // Butted against the front.
4447  //
4448 
4449  AllocationPosition = 0;
4450  }
4451  else if (((PCHAR)Va + (SizeInPages << PAGE_SHIFT)) == ((PCHAR)Entry + (FreePageInfo->Size << PAGE_SHIFT))) {
4452 
4453  //
4454  // Butted against the end.
4455  //
4456 
4457  AllocationPosition = 2;
4458  }
4459  else {
4460 
4461  //
4462  // Somewhere in the middle.
4463  //
4464 
4465  AllocationPosition = 1;
4466  }
4467 
4468  //
4469  // Pages are being removed from the front of
4470  // the list entry and the whole list entry
4471  // will be removed and then the remainder inserted.
4472  //
4473 
4474  //
4475  // Mark start and end for the block at the top of the
4476  // list.
4477  //
4478 
4479  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(Va)) {
4480 
4481  //
4482  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
4483  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
4484  //
4485 
4486  PointerPte = NULL;
4487  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (Va));
4488  }

4490  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress(Va);
4491  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);

4493  }

4496  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
4497  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
4498  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;

4502  // these pages are contiguous, just add to the PFN.
4503  //

4507  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
4508  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0);
4509  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;

4512

4515  //
4516 
4517  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock,
4518  OldIrql);
4519

4522  }

4525

4530  // came from the front or the middle.
4531  //

4534  SpanInPages = FreePageInfo->Size - SizeInPages -
4535  (((ULONG_PTR)Va - (ULONG_PTR)Entry) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
4536

4538  // Mark start and end of the allocation in the PFN database.
4539  //
4540

4542 
4543  //

4545  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
4546  //
4547

4549  }

4552  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4553  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
4554  }
4555 
4556  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
4557  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
4558  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
4559  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;

4563  // these pages being physically contiguous.
4564  //
4565

4567  Pfn1 += (SpanInPages - 1);
4568  }
4569  else {
4570  PointerPte += (SpanInPages - 1);
4571  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4572  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
4573  }
4574  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0);
4575  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;

4578

4580  }

4583  BaseAddress = NULL;
4584

4586 
4587  //
4588  // The front piece needs to be freed as the removal
4589  // came from the middle or the end.
4590  //
4591 
4592  BaseAddress = (PVOID)Entry;
4593 
4594  SpanInPages = ((ULONG_PTR)Va - (ULONG_PTR)Entry) >> PAGE_SHIFT;
4595 
4596  //
4597  // Mark start and end of the allocation in the PFN database.
4598  //
4599 
4600  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
4601 
4602  //
4603  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
4604  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
4605  //
4606 
4607  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (BaseAddress));
4608  }
4609  else {
4610  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress(BaseAddress);
4611  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4612  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
4613  }
4614 
4615  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation == 0);
4616  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);
4617  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation == 0);
4618  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;
4619

4622  // these pages being physically contiguous.
4623  //
4624 
4625  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
4626  Pfn1 += (SpanInPages - 1);
4627  }
4628  else {
4629  PointerPte += (SpanInPages - 1);
4630  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
4631  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPte->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
4632  }
4633  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation == 0);
4634  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;
4635

4637  }

4641  //
4642 
4643  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock,
4644  OldIrql);
4645 
4646  //
4647  // Free the split entry at BaseAddress back into the pool.
4648  // Note that we have overcharged the pool - the entire free
4649  // chunk has been billed. Here we return the piece we
4650  // didn't use and correct the momentary overbilling.
4651  //
4652  // The start and end allocation bits of this split entry
4653  // which we just set up enable ExFreePool and his callees
4654  // to correctly adjust the billing.
4655  //
4656

4658  ExInsertPoolTag ('tnoC',
4659  BaseAddress,

4661  NonPagedPool);
4662  ExFreePool (BaseAddress);
4663  }
4664  if (BaseAddress2) {
4665  ExInsertPoolTag ('tnoC',
4666  BaseAddress2,
4667  SpanInPages2 << PAGE_SHIFT,
4668  NonPagedPool);
4669  ExFreePool (BaseAddress2);
4670  }
4671  BaseAddress = Va;
4672  goto Done;
4673  }
4674  }
4675  Entry = FreePageInfo->List.Flink;
4676  if (MmProtectFreedNonPagedPool == TRUE) {
4677  MiProtectFreeNonPagedPool ((PVOID)FreePageInfo,
4678  (ULONG)FreePageInfo->Size);
4679  }
4680  }
4681  Index += 1;
4682  }
4683 
4684  //
4685  // No entry was found in free nonpaged pool that meets the requirements.
4686  //
4687 
4688  KeReleaseQueuedSpinLock (LockQueueMmNonPagedPoolLock, OldIrql);
4689 
4690 Done:
4691 
4692  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
4693 
4694  if (BaseAddress) {
4695 
4696  MiInsertContiguousTag (BaseAddress,
4697  SizeInPages << PAGE_SHIFT,
4698  CallingAddress);
4699 
4700  ExInsertPoolTag ('tnoC',
4701  BaseAddress,
4702  SizeInPages << PAGE_SHIFT,
4703  NonPagedPool);
4704  }
4705 
4706  return BaseAddress;
4707 }
4708 
4709 PFN_NUMBER
4710 MiFindContiguousPages (
4711  IN PFN_NUMBER LowestPfn,
4712  IN PFN_NUMBER HighestPfn,
4713  IN PFN_NUMBER BoundaryPfn,
4714  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages,
4715  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType
4716  )
4717 
4718 /*++
4719 
4720 Routine Description:
4721 
4722  This function searches nonpaged pool and the free, zeroed,
4723  and standby lists for contiguous pages that satisfy the
4724  request.
4725 
4726  Note no virtual address space is used (thus nonpaged pool is not scanned).
4727  A physical frame number (the caller can map it if he wants to) is returned.
4728 
4729 Arguments:
4730 
4731  LowestPfn - Supplies the lowest acceptable physical page number.
4732 
4733  HighestPfn - Supplies the highest acceptable physical page number.
4734 
4735  BoundaryPfn - Supplies the page frame number multiple the allocation must
4736  not cross. 0 indicates it can cross any boundary.
4737 
4738  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to allocate.
4739 
4740  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping that will be used for the
4741  memory.
4742 
4743 Return Value:
4744 
4745  0 - a contiguous range could not be found to satisfy the request.
4746 
4747  Nonzero - Returns the base physical frame number to the allocated
4748  physically contiguous memory.
4749 
4750 Environment:
4751 
4752  Kernel mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
4753 
4754  Note that in addition to being called at normal runtime, this routine
4755  is also called during Phase 0 initialization before the loaded module
4756  list has been initialized - therefore this routine cannot be made PAGELK
4757  as we wouldn't know how to find it to ensure it was resident.
4758 
4759 --*/
4760 
4761 {
4762  PMMPTE DummyPte;
4763  PKTHREAD Thread;
4764  PMMPFN Pfn1;
4765  PMMPFN EndPfn;
4766  KIRQL OldIrql;
4767  ULONG start;
4768  PFN_NUMBER count;
4769  PFN_NUMBER Page;
4770  PFN_NUMBER LastPage;
4771  PFN_NUMBER found;
4772  PFN_NUMBER BoundaryMask;
4773  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
4774  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
4775  ULONG RetryCount;
4776  LOGICAL FlushedTb;
4777 
4778  PAGED_CODE ();
4779 
4780  ASSERT (SizeInPages != 0);
4781 
4782  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, 0);
4783 
4784  BoundaryMask = ~(BoundaryPfn - 1);
4785 
4786  Pfn1 = NULL;
4787  DummyPte = MiGetPteAddress (MmNonPagedPoolExpansionStart);
4788 
4789  //
4790  // Manually search for a page range which meets the requirements.
4791  //
4792 
4793  Thread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
4794 
4795  KeEnterGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
4796 
4797  MI_LOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
4798 
4799  //
4800  // Charge commitment.
4801  //
4802  // Then search the PFN database for pages that meet the requirements.
4803  //
4804 
4805  if (MiChargeCommitmentCantExpand (SizeInPages, FALSE) == FALSE) {
4806  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
4807  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
4808  return 0;
4809  }
4810 
4811  //
4812  // Charge resident available pages.
4813  //
4814 
4815  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4816 
4817  MiDeferredUnlockPages (MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD);
4818 
4819  if ((SPFN_NUMBER)SizeInPages > MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE()) {
4820  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4821  goto Failed;
4822  }
4823 
4824  //
4825  // Systems utilizing memory compression may have more
4826  // pages on the zero, free and standby lists than we
4827  // want to give out. Explicitly check MmAvailablePages
4828  // instead (and recheck whenever the PFN lock is released
4829  // and reacquired).
4830  //
4831

4833  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);

4838

4840 
4841  RetryCount = 4;
4842

4844 
4845  start = 0;
4846  found = 0;

4849 
4850  count = MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->Run[start].PageCount;
4851  Page = MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->Run[start].BasePage;
4852 
4853  //
4854  // Close the gaps, then examine the range for a fit.
4855  //
4856 
4857  LastPage = Page + count;
4858 
4859  if (LastPage - 1 > HighestPfn) {
4860  LastPage = HighestPfn + 1;
4861  }
4862 
4863  if (Page < LowestPfn) {
4864  Page = LowestPfn;
4865  }
4866 
4867  if ((count != 0) && (Page + SizeInPages <= LastPage)) {
4868 
4869  //

4871  // are on the right list.
4872  //
4873 
4874  found = 0;
4875  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page);
4876 
4877  for ( ; Page < LastPage; Page += 1, Pfn1 += 1) {
4878 
4879  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation <= StandbyPageList) &&
4880  (Pfn1->u1.Flink != 0) &&
4881  (Pfn1->u2.Blink != 0) &&
4882  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) &&
4883  ((CacheAttribute == MiCached) || (Pfn1->u4.MustBeCached == 0))) {
4884 
4885  //
4886  // Before starting a new run, ensure that it
4887  // can satisfy the boundary requirements (if any).
4888  //
4889 
4890  if ((found == 0) && (BoundaryPfn != 0)) {
4891  if (((Page ^ (Page + SizeInPages - 1)) & BoundaryMask) != 0) {
4892  //
4893  // This run's physical address does not meet the
4894  // requirements.
4895  //

4898  }
4899  }
4900 
4901  found += 1;
4902 
4903  if (found == SizeInPages) {
4904

4906  // Lock the PFN database and see if the pages are
4907  // still available for us. Note the invariant
4908  // condition (boundary conformance) does not need
4909  // to be checked again as it was already checked
4910  // above.
4911  //
4912 
4913  Pfn1 -= (found - 1);
4914  Page -= (found - 1);
4915 
4916  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
4917 
4918  do {
4919 
4920  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation <= StandbyPageList) &&
4921  (Pfn1->u1.Flink != 0) &&
4922  (Pfn1->u2.Blink != 0) &&
4923  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) &&

4925

4927  }
4928  else {
4929  break;
4930  }

4935 
4936  //
4937  // All the pages matched the criteria, keep the
4938  // PFN lock, remove them and map them for our
4939  // caller.
4940  //
4941

4946  Page += 1;
4947

4951 
4952  //
4953  // Restart the search at the first possible page.
4954  //
4955

4957  }
4958  }
4959  else {

4961  }
4962  }

4965

4970  //

4974 
4975  goto Failed;
4976  }
4977 
4978  InterlockedIncrement (&MiDelayPageFaults);

4982  // gradually increasing aggressiveness so as not to prematurely

4984  //
4985 
4986  switch (RetryCount) {
4987 
4988  case 4:
4989  MmEmptyAllWorkingSets ();
4990  break;
4991 
4992  case 3:
4993  MiFlushAllPages ();
4994  KeDelayExecutionThread (KernelMode,
4995  FALSE,
4996  (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmHalfSecond);
4997  break;
4998 
4999  case 2:
5000  MmEmptyAllWorkingSets ();
5001  MiFlushAllPages ();
5002  KeDelayExecutionThread (KernelMode,
5003  FALSE,
5004  (PLARGE_INTEGER)&MmOneSecond);

5012  //

5055  break;
5056 
5057  default:

5062

5066  }

5070  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5071  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5072 
5073  MiReturnCommitment (SizeInPages);
5074

5076 
5077 Success:
5078 
5079  ASSERT (start != MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->NumberOfRuns);
5080 
5081  //
5082  // A match has been found, remove these pages
5083  // and return. The PFN lock is held.
5084  //
5085 
5086  //
5087  // Systems utilizing memory compression may have more
5088  // pages on the zero, free and standby lists than we
5089  // want to give out. Explicitly check MmAvailablePages
5090  // instead (and recheck whenever the PFN lock is
5091  // released and reacquired).
5092  //
5093

5095  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5096  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (SizeInPages, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_CONTIGUOUS);
5097  MiReturnCommitment (SizeInPages);
5098  goto Failed;
5099  }

5102 
5103  FlushedTb = FALSE;

5105  do {

5107  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == StandbyPageList) {
5108  MiUnlinkPageFromList (Pfn1);

5112  else {

5117  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount = 1;

5126  // what virtual address(es) this physical frame was last mapped at.
5127  //

5129  // this loop already because the PFN lock is held throughout.
5130  //
5131 
5132  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != CacheAttribute) && (FlushedTb == FALSE)) {
5133  PageFrameIndex = Pfn1 - MmPfnDatabase;
5134  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_INDIVIDUAL_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (PageFrameIndex,
5135  CacheAttribute);

5137  }
5138

5140  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 0;
5141  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 0;
5142  Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation = 0;
5143  Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte = 0;
5144  Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation = 0;

5148  // won't crash. The real value is put in after the loop.
5149  //
5150 
5151  Pfn1->PteAddress = DummyPte;
5152 
5153  if (Pfn1 == EndPfn) {
5154  break;
5155  }
5156 
5157  Pfn1 -= 1;
5158 
5159  } while (TRUE);
5160 
5161  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;
5162  (Pfn1 + SizeInPages - 1)->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;
5163 
5164  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5165 
5166  EndPfn = Pfn1 + SizeInPages;
5167  ASSERT (EndPfn == MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page + 1));
5168 
5169  Page = Page - SizeInPages + 1;
5170  ASSERT (Pfn1 == MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page));
5171  ASSERT (Page != 0);
5172 
5173  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_CONTIGUOUS_PAGES, SizeInPages);
5174 
5175  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5176  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5177 
5178  return Page;
5179 }

5182 VOID
5183 MiFreeContiguousPages (
5184  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
5185  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages
5186  )
5187 
5188 /*++
5189 
5190 Routine Description:
5191 
5192  This function frees the specified physical page range, returning both
5193  commitment and resident available.
5194 
5195 Arguments:
5196 
5197  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the starting physical page number.
5198 
5199  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to free.
5200 
5201 Return Value:
5202 
5203  None.
5204 
5205 Environment:
5206 
5207  Kernel mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
5208 
5209  This is callable from MiReloadBootLoadedDrivers->MiUseDriverLargePages
5210  during Phase 0. ExPageLockHandle and other variables won't exist at
5211  this point, so don't get too fancy here.
5212 
5213 --*/

5216  KIRQL OldIrql;
5217  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5218  PMMPFN EndPfn;
5219 
5220  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= APC_LEVEL);
5221 
5222  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5223  EndPfn = Pfn1 + SizeInPages;
5224 
5225  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5226 
5227  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 0;
5228  (EndPfn - 1)->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 0;
5229 
5230  do {
5231  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED (Pfn1);
5232  MiDecrementShareCount (Pfn1, PageFrameIndex);
5233  PageFrameIndex += 1;
5234  Pfn1 += 1;
5235  } while (Pfn1 < EndPfn);
5236 
5237  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5238 
5239  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (SizeInPages, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_CONTIGUOUS);
5240 
5241  MiReturnCommitment (SizeInPages);
5242 
5243  return;
5244 }

5247 PVOID
5248 MiFindContiguousMemory (
5249  IN PFN_NUMBER LowestPfn,
5250  IN PFN_NUMBER HighestPfn,
5251  IN PFN_NUMBER BoundaryPfn,
5252  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages,
5253  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType,
5254  IN PVOID CallingAddress
5255  )
5256 
5257 /*++
5258 
5259 Routine Description:
5260 
5261  This function searches nonpaged pool and the free, zeroed,
5262  and standby lists for contiguous pages that satisfy the
5263  request.
5264 
5265 Arguments:
5266 
5267  LowestPfn - Supplies the lowest acceptable physical page number.
5268 
5269  HighestPfn - Supplies the highest acceptable physical page number.
5270 
5271  BoundaryPfn - Supplies the page frame number multiple the allocation must
5272  not cross. 0 indicates it can cross any boundary.
5273 
5274  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to allocate.
5275 
5276  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping that will be used for the
5277  memory.
5278 
5279  CallingAddress - Supplies the calling address of the allocator.
5280 
5281 Return Value:
5282 
5283  NULL - a contiguous range could not be found to satisfy the request.
5284 
5285  NON-NULL - Returns a pointer (virtual address in the nonpaged portion
5286  of the system) to the allocated physically contiguous
5287  memory.
5288 
5289 Environment:
5290 
5291  Kernel mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
5292 
5293 --*/
5294 {
5295  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5296  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5297  PMMPFN EndPfn;
5298  PVOID BaseAddress;
5299  PFN_NUMBER Page;
5300  PHYSICAL_ADDRESS PhysicalAddress;
5301  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
5302 
5303  PAGED_CODE ();
5304 
5305  ASSERT (SizeInPages != 0);
5306 
5307  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, 0);
5308 
5309  if (CacheAttribute == MiCached) {
5310 
5311  BaseAddress = MiFindContiguousMemoryInPool (LowestPfn,
5312  HighestPfn,
5313  BoundaryPfn,
5314  SizeInPages,
5315  CallingAddress);
5316  //
5317  // An existing range of nonpaged pool satisfies the requirements
5318  // so return it now.
5319  //
5320 
5321  if (BaseAddress != NULL) {
5322  return BaseAddress;
5323  }
5324  }
5325 
5326  //
5327  // Suitable pool was not allocated via the pool allocator.
5328  // Manually search for a page range which meets the requirements.
5329  //
5330 
5331  Page = MiFindContiguousPages (LowestPfn,
5332  HighestPfn,
5333  BoundaryPfn,
5334  SizeInPages,
5335  CacheType);
5336 
5337  if (Page == 0) {
5338  return NULL;
5339  }
5340 
5341  PhysicalAddress.QuadPart = Page;
5342  PhysicalAddress.QuadPart = PhysicalAddress.QuadPart << PAGE_SHIFT;
5343 
5344  BaseAddress = MmMapIoSpace (PhysicalAddress,
5345  SizeInPages << PAGE_SHIFT,
5346  CacheType);
5347 
5348  if (BaseAddress == NULL) {
5349  MiFreeContiguousPages (Page, SizeInPages);
5350  return NULL;
5351  }
5352 
5353  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page);
5354  EndPfn = Pfn1 + SizeInPages;
5355 
5356  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
5357  do {
5358  Pfn1->PteAddress = PointerPte;
5359  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (MiGetPteAddress(PointerPte));
5360  Pfn1 += 1;
5361  PointerPte += 1;
5362  } while (Pfn1 < EndPfn);
5363 
5364  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_CONTIGUOUS_PAGES, SizeInPages);
5365 
5366  MiInsertContiguousTag (BaseAddress,
5367  SizeInPages << PAGE_SHIFT,
5368  CallingAddress);
5369 
5370  return BaseAddress;
5371 }
