5373 
5374 PFN_NUMBER
5375 MiFindLargePageMemory (
5376  IN PCOLORED_PAGE_INFO ColoredPageInfoBase,
5377  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages,
5378  IN MM_PROTECTION_MASK ProtectionMask,
5379  OUT PPFN_NUMBER OutZeroCount
5380  )
5381 
5382 /*++
5383 
5384 Routine Description:
5385 
5386  This function searches the free, zeroed, standby and modified lists
5387  for contiguous pages to satisfy the request.
5388 
5389  Note the caller must zero the pages on return if these are made visible
5390  to the user.
5391 
5392 Arguments:
5393 
5394  ColoredPageInfoBase - Supplies the colored page info structure to hang
5395  allocated pages off of. This allows the caller to
5396  zero only pages that need zeroing, and to easily
5397  do those in parallel.
5398 
5399  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to allocate.
5400 
5401  ProtectionMask - Supplies the protection mask the caller is going to use.
5402 
5403  OutZeroCount - Receives the number of pages that need to be zeroed.
5404 
5405 Return Value:
5406 
5407  0 - a contiguous range could not be found to satisfy the request.
5408 
5409  NON-0 - Returns the starting page frame number of the allocated physically
5410  contiguous memory.
5411 
5412 Environment:
5413 
5414  Kernel mode, APCs disabled, AddressCreation mutex held.
5415 
5416  The caller must bring in PAGELK.
5417 
5418  The caller has already charged commitment for the range (typically by
5419  virtue of the VAD insert) so no commit is charged here.
5420 
5421 --*/
5422 {
5423  ULONG Color;
5424  PKTHREAD Thread;
5425  ULONG CurrentNodeColor;
5426  PFN_NUMBER ZeroCount;
5427  LOGICAL NeedToZero;
5428  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5429  PMMPFN EndPfn;
5430  PMMPFN BoundaryPfn;
5431  KIRQL OldIrql;
5432  ULONG start;
5433  PFN_NUMBER count;
5434  PFN_NUMBER Page;
5435  PFN_NUMBER NewPage;
5436  PFN_NUMBER LastPage;
5437  PFN_NUMBER found;
5438  PFN_NUMBER BoundaryMask;
5439  PCOLORED_PAGE_INFO ColoredPageInfo;
5440  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
5441  MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType;
5442  LOGICAL FlushTbNeeded;
5443 
5444  FlushTbNeeded = FALSE;
5445 
5446  PAGED_CODE ();
5447 
5448 #ifdef _X86_
5449  ASSERT (KeFeatureBits & KF_LARGE_PAGE);
5450 #endif
5451 
5452  ASSERT (SizeInPages != 0);
5453 
5454  BoundaryMask = (PFN_NUMBER) ((MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT) - 1);
5455 
5456  start = 0;
5457  found = 0;
5458  Pfn1 = NULL;
5459  ZeroCount = 0;
5460 
5461  CacheType = MmCached;
5462  if (MI_IS_NOCACHE (ProtectionMask)) {
5463  CacheType = MmNonCached;
5464  }
5465  else if (MI_IS_WRITECOMBINE (ProtectionMask)) {
5466  CacheType = MmWriteCombined;
5467  }
5468 
5469  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, 0);
5470 
5471  //
5472  // Charge resident available pages.
5473  //
5474 
5475  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5476 
5477  MiDeferredUnlockPages (MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD);
5478 
5479  if ((SPFN_NUMBER)SizeInPages > MI_NONPAGEABLE_MEMORY_AVAILABLE()) {
5480  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5481  return 0;
5482  }
5483 
5484  //
5485  // Systems utilizing memory compression may have more
5486  // pages on the zero, free and standby lists than we
5487  // want to give out. Explicitly check MmAvailablePages
5488  // instead (and recheck whenever the PFN lock is released
5489  // and reacquired).
5490  //
5491 
5492  if ((SPFN_NUMBER)SizeInPages > (SPFN_NUMBER)(MmAvailablePages - MM_HIGH_LIMIT)) {
5493  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5494  return 0;
5495  }
5496 
5497  MI_DECREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (SizeInPages, MM_RESAVAIL_ALLOCATE_LARGE_PAGES);
5498 
5499  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5500 
5501  Page = 0;
5502 
5503  //
5504  // Search the PFN database for pages that meet the requirements.
5505  // For NUMA configurations, try the current local node first.
5506  //
5507 
5508 #define ANY_COLOR_OK 0xFFFFFFFF // Indicate any color is ok.
5509 
5510  CurrentNodeColor = ANY_COLOR_OK;
5511 
5512 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
5513  if (KeNumberNodes > 1) {
5514  CurrentNodeColor = KeGetCurrentPrcb()->NodeColor;
5515  }
5516 #endif
5517 
5518  Thread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
5519 
5520  KeEnterGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5521 
5522  MI_LOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5523 
5524 rescan:
5525 
5526  for ( ; start != MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->NumberOfRuns; start += 1) {
5527 
5528  count = MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->Run[start].PageCount;
5529  Page = MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->Run[start].BasePage;
5530 
5531  //
5532  // Close the gaps, then examine the range for a fit.
5533  //
5534 
5535  LastPage = Page + count;
5536 
5537  if ((Page & BoundaryMask) || (Page == 0)) {
5538  NewPage = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (Page, (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT));
5539 
5540  if (NewPage < Page) {
5541  continue;
5542  }
5543 
5544  Page = NewPage;
5545 
5546  if (Page == 0) {
5547  Page = (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
5548  }
5549 
5550  if (Page >= LastPage) {
5551  continue;
5552  }
5553  }
5554 
5555  if (LastPage & BoundaryMask) {
5556  LastPage &= ~BoundaryMask;
5557 
5558  if (Page >= LastPage) {
5559  continue;
5560  }
5561  }
5562 
5563  if (Page + SizeInPages > LastPage) {
5564  continue;
5565  }
5566 
5567  count = LastPage - Page + 1;
5568 
5569  ASSERT (count != 0);
5570 
5571  //
5572  // A fit may be possible in this run, check whether the pages
5573  // are on the right list.
5574  //
5575 
5576  found = 0;
5577  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page);
5578 
5579  while (Page < LastPage) {
5580 
5581  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation <= StandbyPageList) &&
5582  (Pfn1->u1.Flink != 0) &&
5583  (Pfn1->u2.Blink != 0) &&
5584  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0) &&
5585  ((CurrentNodeColor == ANY_COLOR_OK) ||
5586  (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageColor == CurrentNodeColor))) {
5587 
5588  found += 1;
5589 
5590  if (found == SizeInPages) {
5591 
5592  //
5593  // Lock the PFN database and see if the pages are
5594  // still available for us.
5595  //
5596 
5597  Pfn1 -= (found - 1);
5598  Page -= (found - 1);
5599 
5600  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5601 
5602  do {
5603 
5604  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation <= StandbyPageList) &&
5605  (Pfn1->u1.Flink != 0) &&
5606  (Pfn1->u2.Blink != 0) &&
5607  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0)) {
5608 
5609  NOTHING; // Good page
5610  }
5611  else {
5612  break;
5613  }
5614 
5615  found -= 1;
5616 
5617  if (found == 0) {
5618 
5619  //
5620  // All the pages matched the criteria, keep the
5621  // PFN lock, remove them and map them for our
5622  // caller.
5623  //
5624 
5625  goto Done;
5626  }
5627 
5628  Pfn1 += 1;
5629  Page += 1;
5630 
5631  } while (TRUE);
5632 
5633 #if DBG
5634  if (MiShowStuckPages != 0) {
5635  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
5636  "MiFindLargePages : could not claim stolen PFN %p\n",
5637  Page);
5638  if (MiShowStuckPages & 0x8) {
5639  DbgBreakPoint ();
5640  }
5641  }
5642 #endif
5643  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5644 
5645  //
5646  // Restart the search at the first possible page.
5647  //
5648 
5649  found = 0;
5650  }
5651  }
5652  else {
5653 #if DBG
5654  if (MiShowStuckPages != 0) {
5655  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_INFO_LEVEL,
5656  "MiFindLargePages : could not claim PFN %p %x %x\n",
5657  Page, Pfn1->u3.e1, Pfn1->u4.EntireFrame);
5658  if (MiShowStuckPages & 0x8) {
5659  DbgBreakPoint ();
5660  }
5661  }
5662 #endif
5663  found = 0;
5664  }
5665 
5666  Page += 1;
5667  Pfn1 += 1;
5668 
5669  if (found == 0) {
5670 
5671  //
5672  // The last page interrogated wasn't available so skip
5673  // ahead to the next acceptable boundary.
5674  //
5675 
5676  NewPage = MI_ROUND_TO_SIZE (Page,
5677  (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT));
5678 
5679  if ((NewPage == 0) || (NewPage < Page) || (NewPage >= LastPage)) {
5680 
5681  //
5682  // Skip the rest of this entry.
5683  //
5684 
5685  Page = LastPage;
5686  continue;
5687  }
5688 
5689  Page = NewPage;
5690  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page);
5691  }
5692  }
5693  }
5694 
5695  //
5696  // The desired physical pages could not be allocated. If we were trying
5697  // for local memory (ie: NUMA machine), then expand our search to include
5698  // any node and try one last time.
5699  //
5700 
5701  if (CurrentNodeColor != ANY_COLOR_OK) {
5702  CurrentNodeColor = ANY_COLOR_OK;
5703  start = 0;
5704  found = 0;
5705  goto rescan;
5706  }
5707 
5708  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5709  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5710  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (SizeInPages, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LARGE_PAGES);
5711  return 0;
5712 
5713 Done:
5714 
5715  //
5716  // A match has been found, remove these pages,
5717  // map them and return. The PFN lock is held.
5718  //
5719 
5720  ASSERT (start != MmPhysicalMemoryBlock->NumberOfRuns);
5721  ASSERT (Page - SizeInPages + 1 != 0);
5722 
5723  //
5724  // Systems utilizing memory compression may have more
5725  // pages on the zero, free and standby lists than we
5726  // want to give out. Explicitly check MmAvailablePages
5727  // instead (and recheck whenever the PFN lock is
5728  // released and reacquired).
5729  //
5730 
5731  if ((SPFN_NUMBER)SizeInPages > (SPFN_NUMBER)(MmAvailablePages - MM_HIGH_LIMIT)) {
5732  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5733  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (SizeInPages, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_LARGE_PAGES);
5734 
5735  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5736  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5737 
5738  return 0;
5739  }
5740 
5741  EndPfn = Pfn1 - SizeInPages + 1;
5742 
5743  BoundaryPfn = Pfn1 - (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
5744 
5745  do {
5746 
5747  NeedToZero = TRUE;
5748 
5749  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == StandbyPageList) {
5750  MiUnlinkPageFromList (Pfn1);
5751  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount == 0);
5752  MiRestoreTransitionPte (Pfn1);
5753  }
5754  else {
5755  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ZeroedPageList) {
5756  NeedToZero = FALSE;
5757  }
5758  MiUnlinkFreeOrZeroedPage (Pfn1);
5759  }
5760 
5761  Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount = 1;
5762  Pfn1->u2.ShareCount = 1;
5763  MI_SET_PFN_DELETED(Pfn1);
5764  Pfn1->u4.PteFrame = MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME;
5765  Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation = ActiveAndValid;
5766 
5767  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute != CacheAttribute) {
5768  FlushTbNeeded = TRUE;
5769  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = CacheAttribute;
5770  }
5771 
5772  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 0;
5773  Pfn1->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 0;
5774  Pfn1->u4.VerifierAllocation = 0;
5775  Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation = 0;
5776 
5777  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.AweAllocation == 0);
5778  Pfn1->u4.AweAllocation = 1;
5779 
5780  Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte = 0;
5781 
5782  //
5783  // Add free and standby pages to the list of pages to be zeroed
5784  // by our caller.
5785  //
5786 
5787  if (NeedToZero == TRUE) {
5788  Color = MI_GET_COLOR_FROM_LIST_ENTRY (Page, Pfn1);
5789 
5790  ColoredPageInfo = &ColoredPageInfoBase[Color];
5791 
5792  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = (ULONG_PTR) ColoredPageInfo->PfnAllocation;
5793  ColoredPageInfo->PfnAllocation = Pfn1;
5794  ColoredPageInfo->PagesQueued += 1;
5795  ZeroCount += 1;
5796  }
5797  else {
5798  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
5799  }
5800 
5801  if (Pfn1 == EndPfn) {
5802  break;
5803  }
5804 
5805  Pfn1 -= 1;
5806 
5807  if (Pfn1 == BoundaryPfn) {
5808  BoundaryPfn = Pfn1 - (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
5809  }
5810 
5811  } while (TRUE);
5812 
5813  Pfn1->u3.e1.StartOfAllocation = 1;
5814  (Pfn1 + SizeInPages - 1)->u3.e1.EndOfAllocation = 1;
5815 
5816  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5817 
5818  MI_UNLOCK_DYNAMIC_MEMORY_SHARED ();
5819  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (Thread);
5820 
5821  if (FlushTbNeeded) {
5822  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB_FOR_ATTRIBUTE_CHANGE (CacheAttribute);
5823  }
5824 
5825  Page = Page - SizeInPages + 1;
5826  ASSERT (Page != 0);
5827  ASSERT (Pfn1 == MI_PFN_ELEMENT (Page));
5828 
5829  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_CHARGE_LARGE_PAGES, SizeInPages);
5830 
5831  *OutZeroCount = ZeroCount;
5832  return Page;
5833 }
5834 
5835 
5836 VOID
5837 MiFreeLargePageMemory (
5838  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
5839  IN PFN_NUMBER SizeInPages
5840  )
5841 
5842 /*++
5843 
5844 Routine Description:
5845 
5846  This function returns a contiguous large page allocation to the free
5847  memory lists.
5848 
5849 Arguments:
5850 
5851  VirtualAddress - Supplies the starting page frame index to free.
5852 
5853  SizeInPages - Supplies the number of pages to free.
5854 
5855 Return Value:
5856 
5857  None.
5858 
5859 Environment:
5860 
5861  Kernel mode, IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below.
5862 
5863 --*/
5864 {
5865  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5866  KIRQL OldIrql;
5867  PKTHREAD CurrentThread;
5868  PFN_NUMBER LastPageFrameIndex;
5869  LONG EntryCount;
5870  LONG OriginalCount;
5871  LOGICAL FlushTbNeeded;
5872 
5873  PAGED_CODE ();
5874 
5875  ASSERT (SizeInPages != 0);
5876 
5877  LastPageFrameIndex = PageFrameIndex + SizeInPages;
5878 
5879  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5880 
5881  FlushTbNeeded = FALSE;
5882 
5883  //
5884  // The actual commitment for this range (and its page table pages, etc)
5885  // is released when the vad is removed. Because we will release commitment
5886  // below for each physical page, temporarily increase the charge now so
5887  // it all balances out. Block user APCs so a suspend can't stop us.
5888  //
5889 
5890  CurrentThread = KeGetCurrentThread ();
5891 
5892  KeEnterCriticalRegionThread (CurrentThread);
5893 
5894  MiChargeCommitmentCantExpand (SizeInPages, TRUE);
5895 
5896  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5897 
5898  do {
5899  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 1);
5900  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid);
5901 
5902  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.LargeSessionAllocation == 0);

5945  // calling MmUnlockPages. All threads can safely do
5946  // interlocked decrements on the "AWE reference count".
5947  // Whichever thread drives it to zero is responsible for
5948  // decrementing the actual PFN reference count (which may
5949  // be greater than 1 due to other non-AWE API calls being
5950  // used on the same page). The thread that drives this

5980  // periodically to allow other processors and DPCs a chance to execute.
5981  //

5987  FlushTbNeeded = FALSE;
5988  }
5989

5991 
5992  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
5993  }
5994 
5995  Pfn1 += 1;
5996  PageFrameIndex += 1;
5997 
5998  } while (PageFrameIndex < LastPageFrameIndex);
5999

6001  MI_FLUSH_TB_FOR_CACHED_ATTRIBUTE ();
6002  }
6003 
6004  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
6005
